---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Open Signal — free, AI-powered intelligence for everyone.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--spacing-article)] px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="mb-8" style="font-size: var(--text-4xl);">About Open Signal</h1>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Mission</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Open Signal exists to prove that high-quality intelligence and analysis can be free.
          No paywalls. No ads. No subscription gates. No sponsored content.
        </p>
        <p>
          The best analysis in tech, AI, and strategy has historically been locked behind
          expensive subscriptions or buried in noise. We believe access to clear, well-sourced
          insight should not be a privilege reserved for those who can afford it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-accent);">How it works</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Every piece of content on Open Signal is generated by AI, reviewed for accuracy,
          and published on a regular cadence. Our five content pillars cover different depths
          and formats:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Deep Signals</strong> &mdash; Flagship analysis pieces covering technology and strategy</li>
          <li><strong>Signal Briefings</strong> &mdash; Daily intelligence briefings with the most important developments</li>
          <li><strong>Signal Maps</strong> &mdash; Visual and structural explainers of markets and technology landscapes</li>
          <li><strong>The Long View</strong> &mdash; Weekend deep dives into long-term trends and strategic themes</li>
          <li><strong>Open Source</strong> &mdash; Transparent updates about how the project itself is built</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-accent);">The technology behind it</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Open Signal is built with Astro, styled with Tailwind CSS, and hosted on Vercel.
          Content is authored in MDX and stored in Git. The entire content pipeline &mdash; from
          research to writing to publishing &mdash; is designed to run autonomously with AI at
          the core.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use Claude as the primary AI engine for research, analysis, and writing.
          Every step of the process is transparent and documented.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Open source ethos</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This project is built in the open. The source code, the content pipeline,
          the editorial guidelines, and the automation tooling are all public.
          If you want to understand how an AI-powered publication works end to end,
          everything is available for inspection and learning.
        </p>
        <p>
          We document our process, share our mistakes, and publish our methodology
          because transparency is not just a feature &mdash; it is the foundation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
